  <h1>WELCOME TO THE INFLATION API</h1>
  <div class="wrapper">
    <h3>The Inflation API intended for developers to calculate inflation-adjusted values in current dollars. Currently the API uses the Consumer Price Index, dating back to 1913. This API is RESTful and responses are in JSON format. Future versions will allow developers to choose which ever economic index they prefer.
    <br/><br/>
    Consumer Price Index data is sourced from the <a href="https://www.minneapolisfed.org/community/teaching-aids/cpi-calculator-information/consumer-price-index-and-inflation-rates-1913">Federal Reserve Bank of Minneapolis</a>.
    </h3>
